<article class="hardware">
  <header>
    <h2>Supported Hardware by SoC</h2>
  </header>

  <ul class="nav nav-tabs mb-4">
    <li class="nav-item"><%= link_to "Full list", cameras_vendors_path, class: "nav-link#{" active" if @vendor.blank?}" %></li>
    <% Vendor.order(:name).each do |v| %>
      <li class="nav-item">
        <%= link_to v.name, cameras_vendor_path(v), class: "nav-link#{" active" if @vendor.eql?(v.name)}" %>
      </li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>

  <h3><%= @page_title %></h3>

  <p class="alert alert-warning">If access to bootloader console on your camera is password-protected by manufacturer,
    consider replacing the bootloader with our version of U-Boot.</p>

  <div class="alert alert-danger">
    <h5 class="fw-bold">IMPORTANT! Backup your original firmware!</h5>
    <p class="mb-0">We ship our own upgraded version of the U-Boot boot loader which, once installed, overwrites your original crypto
      partition, making it impossible to revert to the original factory firmware unless you have a full flash backup for
      a specific camera!</p>
  </div>

  <p><a href="/stages-of-firmware-development">Stages of firmware development explained</a></p>

  <div class="socs">
    <dl class="row mb-3 border-bottom small fw-bold">
      <dd class="col-2 col-md-1 stage">Stage</dd>
      <dd class="col-10 col-md-3 model">SoC Model</dd>
      <dd class="col-2 col-md-1 url">Docs</dd>
      <dd class="col-2 col-md-1 url">U-Boot</dd>
      <dd class="col-2 col-md-1 url">Linux</dd>
      <dd class="col-2 col-md-1 url">SDK</dd>
      <dd class="col-4 col-md-2 hex_address">Load address</dd>
      <dd class="col-12 col-md-2">Build status</dd>
    </dl>

    <%= render @socs %>
  </div>
</article>
